IBADAN – The Oyo State government has announced May 5, 2022, as the resumption date for public and private schools in the state. The permanent secretary, Ministry of Education, Science and Technology, Atere A. B, dis­closed this in a circular seen by journalists Tuesday. According to the circular, teaching and learning activi­ties are expected to commence immediately after schools re­sume from the second term holiday. The circular added that the officials of the ministry would be fully deployed to enforce compliance with the directive.